LDTEXT:
@1300 activated duty remotely 

Well interlocked due to influent lolo alarm
@1313 ack reset alarm, when value came back up and well restarted

Onsite to investigate Lo influent

Checked residual mg/l
@0935
Free analyzer 0.98 grab 0.92

@0936 started backflush 

@1000
Influent free analyzer 1.10 grab 1.11

@1002 stopped backflush 
Approximately 19m3

Restarted well in manual at 23l/s
Influent hihi alarm came in 
Reduced dosage factor until residual stabilized

Checked residuals mg/l

Influent free
@1111 
Analyzer 2.79 grab 2.88

Effluent free
@1115
Analyzer 2.26 grab 2.15

On site for monthly PMs. Informed ROC
- Pump #4 (Jockey) monthly maintenance and test run
@13:50 - Started pump #4 for monthly test run (Jockey pump) 
@13:55 - Observed that chlorinator #3 (The chlorinator tied to pump #4 was not dosing.  Found that the discharge valve from the chlorinator was closed.  Opened valve.  Immediately stopped pump #4.  
@14:00 - Started backflushing to waste, added dechlor pucks to outfall 
@14:02 - Effluent free chlorine lolo alarm came in (Pumps are already off)
@14:07 - Free chlorine residual analyzer is reading 1.86 mg/L.  It did not take long to backflush as the jockey pump was only running at 30 L/s for less than 5 minutes.  Stopped backflushing @14:10
@14:13 - restarted pump #4 with chlorinator #3 properly dosing now 
@15:00 - stopped pump #4, left in manual off as per normal
Closed valves on chlorinator #3 as they were found before. Will inquire as to why they are closed.

Station operation normal

On site with GFL for adhoc post aeration tank clean out to retrieve the grating that fell in last week.

Started diverting to lagoon @ 8:25 am, pumping station flow totalizer @ 382m3. Dropped in 2 slide gates to isolate inlet chamber. Slide gate not perfectly water tight, about 10% going pass the gate.

@14:00, Accuworx was able to drawdown the chamber to near bottom. Ops performed CSE to get the grating out. 

@14:15, all gates inserted in the headworks has been removed, valve to clarifier 2 has been re-opened. Both RAS put back in service

@8:30am - Made some changes in response to high flow event.

put pump 2 in duty 3 and increased duty 1 vfd min speed from 15% to 50% to minimize duty 2 start

cleared ultrasonic interlock on pump 3

pump 1 vfd fault outstanding from last night, will be investigated on upcoming station checks.

@12:32 - Put duty 1 vfd min speed back to 15%.

Train #7 had shutdown overnight on MIT low pressure decay failed alarm.  It failed at a 7.66 kpa.  Cleared alarms and initiated another MIT on train #7 @11:26.  

@11:27 - Activated duty 1

Low pressure passed - 5.19 kpa decay
